      "content": "i get that it's complicated, but you didn't really answer me. you're talking about \"nuanced discussion\" and \"middle grounds,\" but that feels like dodging the question. \n\nif we look at the actual outcome of these systems, isn't it true that treating healthcare as a right is the only way to ensure actual equality? it feels like the \"government takeover\" argument is just used to protect corporate profits rather than being a real concern about efficiency. whats your take on that specifically?",
